WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.707
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.707 --> 00:00:02.811
Praise the Lord.

00:00:02.811 --> 00:00:04.799
Thank you for joining me today.

00:00:05.128 --> 00:00:11.260
There is a lot going on again as usual, but I just wanted to say happy Palm Sunday.

00:00:12.100 --> 00:00:18.069
We have one week from today that we are able to celebrate the Lord Jesus Christ and his resurrection.

00:00:18.417 --> 00:00:20.904
What a time of the year it is!

00:00:21.400 --> 00:00:23.600
This is my favorite time of the year, y'all.

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:36.960
I mean, whenever the spring is here, the grass is coming out, all the beautiful trees are budding, and all the birds are coming back from the south, I personally believe, other than fall, it doesn't get better than that.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:40.701
I love fall, too; I love the colors.

00:00:40.701 --> 00:00:44.256
But I'm excited about resurrection Sunday.

00:00:45.360 --> 00:01:00.000
We're going to pray for the protection over the people today for resurrection Sunday, that no terrorist attacks, no plots, and no plans of the evil one would come against us as we go into our houses of worship to worship our risen savior.

00:01:00.462 --> 00:01:05.920
I know that the enemy comes to kill, steal, and destroy, but we have power and authority over him.

00:01:06.196 --> 00:01:11.440
We're not going to allow, in the name of Jesus, any of that to happen in any places of the earth.

00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:23.340
The Lord warned us when I've told you all about praying over the churches in the Middle East, our brothers and sisters in the Middle East, praying over them that they would have safety in this time of worship.

00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:37.680
And even in the United States of America, I know that we keep things at bay as we take our authority, take communion, pray daily, and come before him boldly, taking our rightful place and seat next to him.

00:01:40.959 --> 00:01:43.760
I know a lot of people liked the tithing video.

00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:47.920
I made that; I try to be real with people, but you're not going to appease everybody.

00:01:47.920 --> 00:01:49.299
So, I'm just like, 'Whatever.

00:01:49.299 --> 00:01:50.960
If you like it, you like it; if you don't, you don't.

00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:55.709
' It's what we believe, it's how we live, and this is how I'll continue to live.

00:01:55.709 --> 00:02:03.715
And what I believe is that unless the Holy Spirit corrects me, I'm just going to keep on keeping on because I've been doing it for 20 years.

00:02:03.715 --> 00:02:04.663
So, it is what it is.

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:09.040
People ask me, 'Brandon, what do you believe?

00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:12.418
' So, we just tell you, 'Hey, this is where I'm at.

00:02:12.418 --> 00:02:20.800
' And if I told you the hundredfold ground, you'd get ticked off and wouldn't watch the channels anymore because I know some of the people you can't stand.

00:02:21.120 --> 00:02:27.520
So, we don't even tell you the hundredfold ground, but I know what the hundredfold ground is because I studied it.

00:02:29.759 --> 00:02:40.699
It took me years of sowing and praying and listening to the Holy Spirit and asking him what the hundredfold ground is.

00:02:41.109 --> 00:02:46.869
I found some nuggets, but that came through a lot of spiritual pressure.

00:02:47.872 --> 00:02:57.179
I try to hint around sometimes around these preachers that I know the hundredfold ground's on, and then I know the ones whose ground is bad ground.

00:02:58.080 --> 00:03:01.760
I say it's crap ground that doesn't grow anything at all.

00:03:02.103 --> 00:03:06.320
People really follow some of those folks and they go, 'Oh yeah, they're really good ground.

00:03:06.320 --> 00:03:07.554
' I say, 'No, that ground sucks.

00:03:07.554 --> 00:03:10.479
' I'm just being real.

00:03:10.479 --> 00:03:13.350
Probably not a good word to use, but it's just true.

00:03:13.350 --> 00:03:21.080
And you've got the one ground that's really good and they go, 'We can't stand them because they have jets and they have all this stuff.

00:03:21.080 --> 00:03:34.480
' Folks, I'll give you a hint on some things: if they are successful in ministry, the Bible says if you're faithful with little, God will make you ruler over much.

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.000
So, God is the God of increase.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:41.496
He's the one that brings the increase on folks.

00:03:41.496 --> 00:03:48.920
And if they are walking in abundance, they've been faithful with what they have and God's giving them more.

00:03:48.920 --> 00:04:00.259
So if you see somebody who doesn't have much and their ministry isn't flourishing year after year and they're staying the same, they haven't passed the test.

00:04:00.259 --> 00:04:09.699
It takes you going from glory to glory, and you pass the test, and he gives you more like the talents.

00:04:09.699 --> 00:04:15.463
But you get mad and want to crucify the guy who has more and they go, 'Well, how much do they have?

00:04:15.646 --> 00:04:19.079
They have too much; they must have swindled it out of an old lady.

00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:20.384
' Folks, come on.

00:04:20.384 --> 00:04:22.890
God is the God of increase.

00:04:24.869 --> 00:04:29.400
So, you want to gravitate to the ground.

00:04:29.400 --> 00:04:35.966
If they've been in ministry—not like me, I've been in ministry for a year and a half going on two years.

00:04:35.966 --> 00:04:36.754
Two years, right?

00:04:36.754 --> 00:04:38.133
Wow, time goes fast.

00:04:38.133 --> 00:04:42.370
So I'm just a baby in this, just like a toddler.

00:04:42.370 --> 00:04:57.280
But if you've been in ministry for 30 years and you're still the same and you haven't changed and nothing's going from glory to glory and your capacity hasn't increased to be able to handle or reach more, you haven't passed the test.

00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:05.669
It doesn't make you bad; it just means you need to go through the refiner's fire so that you're able to handle more.

00:05:05.669 --> 00:05:07.760
Does that make sense, what I'm trying to tell you all?

00:05:08.080 --> 00:05:11.714
You see a lot of ministries that don't have any more anointing.

00:05:11.714 --> 00:05:13.086
They don't have any more presence.

00:05:13.086 --> 00:05:15.440
They don't have any more stuff going on for them.

00:05:15.632 --> 00:05:20.400
They keep going on the same way, going around the same mountain all the time.

00:05:20.587 --> 00:05:26.235
You look at them and then you give to their ground and you go, 'Oh, well, I understand.

00:05:26.235 --> 00:05:33.840
' But then you sow to the good ground that is blessed and you go, 'Wow,' and you instantaneously get a big harvest back.

00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:37.760
And I've learned to test the soil.

00:05:39.226 --> 00:05:40.435
I flow that way.

00:05:40.737 --> 00:05:45.700
I tell my wife all the time, 'Let's not go and give a whole bucket load of seed.

00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:53.119
Let's take $100 or $50 and sow it into that ground and see how long it takes.

00:05:53.119 --> 00:05:54.826
' And we'll call that in.

00:05:55.537 --> 00:05:57.800
It's not all on the minister, too.

00:05:57.800 --> 00:06:07.780
By the way, the Holy Spirit said this to me: 'Brandon, you're blaming the harvest solely on the minister, but the sower has part of it, too.

00:06:07.780 --> 00:06:13.449
' It's not all on the person in the soil; it's on the seed sower.

00:06:18.029 --> 00:06:22.880
So you need to know it's a half-and-half responsibility.

00:06:22.880 --> 00:06:41.280
You have to name your seed, you have to water your seed by watering it with the word, calling those things that be not as though they were, keeping strife out of your house, taking communion on a day-to-day basis, and sending your angels forth in the name of Jesus to bring forth your harvest.

00:06:41.280 --> 00:06:51.290
And if you're sitting there just idly by going, 'Well, I'm just waiting for my good truck to come in with all my goods on it.

00:06:51.290 --> 00:06:54.710
Where's my miracle package?

00:06:54.710 --> 00:07:00.604
' I told you the Bible says whatever you put your hands to will prosper.

00:07:00.604 --> 00:07:05.715
So if you've got to put your hand to something, you don't sit by with your thumb in your nose.

00:07:05.715 --> 00:07:08.440
You've got to go out and do something.

00:07:09.340 --> 00:07:11.577
Put your faith in action.

00:07:11.577 --> 00:07:13.627
Faith without works is dead.

00:07:13.627 --> 00:07:16.159
Now I sit there and go, 'Well, I'm just waiting.

00:07:16.159 --> 00:07:18.320
I want my angel to bring my sack of money.

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:24.000
' I told you that's a miracle and that happens, but it's not something that happens all the time.

00:07:24.284 --> 00:07:31.245
I'd say more than what I've ever seen in my life, God says, 'Brandon, go out and get it, buddy.

00:07:31.245 --> 00:07:34.098
Take your hand to it and make it happen.

00:07:34.098 --> 00:07:37.200
But I will bless whatever you put your hands to.

00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:39.799
' Do something with your life.

00:07:39.799 --> 00:07:46.920
You're waiting so much for the ice cream truck to come by, but you've got to go out and get it.

00:07:48.604 --> 00:07:51.525
Go down to Blue Bell and get you some.

00:07:51.525 --> 00:07:55.168
I haven't had ice cream in a while; the Lord won't let me have it.

00:07:57.831 --> 00:08:01.227
So, I'm thinking about it right now.

00:08:01.227 --> 00:08:05.142
It's like, 'Oh, God, help me.

00:08:05.142 --> 00:08:06.291
' Just being real.

00:08:06.291 --> 00:08:13.039
I was thinking about my ice cream, but we're getting over that.

00:08:13.039 --> 00:08:17.600
Anyway, doing these videos...

00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:18.960
okay.

00:08:18.960 --> 00:08:26.560
So, when we see the ground and you're sowing into the ground, look at the fruit that the ground has.

00:08:26.560 --> 00:08:28.373
What's going on around their ministry?

00:08:28.373 --> 00:08:30.239
Is their ministry prospering?

00:08:30.239 --> 00:08:32.832
Is their ministry flourishing?

00:08:32.832 --> 00:08:35.046
Has God anointed them?

00:08:35.046 --> 00:08:42.342
If you see change and souls are coming in like Billy Graham, you know Billy Graham was good soil, right?

00:08:42.342 --> 00:08:44.480
He's not here anymore, so I can use him as an example.

00:08:44.480 --> 00:08:46.880
You won't throw eggs at me.

00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:54.391
Billy Graham's soil—I'm sure at that time, I never sowed into it—was probably very fertile ground because why?

00:08:54.391 --> 00:09:00.160
He was getting a lot of people born again and his ministry was exploding.

00:09:00.160 --> 00:09:03.920
It was like, "Wow, look at what's going on with Billy Graham.

00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:05.200
Everybody knew Billy Graham.

00:09:05.200 --> 00:09:06.689
" He was a household name, right?

00:09:06.689 --> 00:09:15.143
So, if you see somebody and God is really touching them, try it.

00:09:16.720 --> 00:09:18.053
That's all I can say.

00:09:18.053 --> 00:09:18.587
Try it.

00:09:18.587 --> 00:09:30.304
And maybe, just maybe, if you keep your heart right and don't badmouth them, you sit there and think, "God, you're obviously touching this individual for a reason.

00:09:30.304 --> 00:09:32.251
Something's going on with it.

00:09:32.543 --> 00:09:35.140
I'm going to test the ground.

00:09:35.140 --> 00:09:41.360
" Now, if you have some of these others whose ground is their ministry, they're the same.

00:09:41.360 --> 00:09:42.960
Their following hasn't changed.

00:09:56.770 --> 00:09:57.160
If it seems that everything around them is dying, then you have to go.

00:09:57.160 --> 00:10:14.145
There's nothing wrong with small churches, but if the church is not getting any growth, if it is not bringing anybody to get saved, if it's not baptizing, if it's not laying hands on the sick, if it's not casting out devils, I would consider why I'm going to church there.

00:10:14.145 --> 00:10:15.845
Does that make sense?

00:10:15.845 --> 00:10:18.720
You have to be careful where you're going.

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:21.553
Don't go and put yourself in a church that's dead.

00:10:21.553 --> 00:10:23.519
They're not getting any outreach.

00:10:23.519 --> 00:10:25.120
They're not getting anybody saved.

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:28.227
They're just there on a Sunday or Wednesday.

00:10:28.227 --> 00:10:41.528
They have a couple Bible studies and go home, and they're not really into expanding our tent and reaching the nations for Jesus because that's what we're there for anyway.

00:10:41.528 --> 00:10:44.651
I don't want to just have a feel-good sermon.

00:10:46.469 --> 00:10:56.537
Maybe have a potluck; some people have potlucks, you know, they'll have some tables or have some fried chicken or whatever, and they'll eat and have a little fellowship.

00:10:56.537 --> 00:11:00.782
And you walk away and think, "But did we get anybody new saved?

00:11:02.026 --> 00:11:07.955
Did we try?

00:11:08.714 --> 00:11:11.571
Did we help anybody?

00:11:11.571 --> 00:11:17.060
" Year after year, it's the same old thing.

00:11:17.575 --> 00:11:37.058
But if you're trying to expand your borders and you're letting the Holy Ghost flow, and you see people's lives changing—drug addicts or prostitutes or whatever—and they're getting their lives set free, then by all means, man, that's alive.

00:11:37.058 --> 00:11:39.701
I want to be where it's alive.

00:11:39.701 --> 00:11:49.360
I want to see people's lives changed from glory to glory where the Holy Ghost is allowed to move.

00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:50.027
It happens.

00:11:50.027 --> 00:11:51.027
There are churches like that.

00:11:51.027 --> 00:11:53.159
Collinsville is one.

00:11:54.686 --> 00:12:01.360
Pastor Candace and Chip let the Holy Ghost move, but there are some folks that won't.

00:12:03.550 --> 00:12:07.739
I'm trying to paint a picture that it's not all the soil's fault.

00:12:07.739 --> 00:12:14.297
You've got to call in your seed, you've got to water your seed, and you've got to be speaking.

00:12:14.297 --> 00:12:15.600
Don't be speaking double.

00:12:15.600 --> 00:12:18.700
A double-minded man is unstable in all his ways.

00:12:18.700 --> 00:12:22.128
You can't be saying, "Well, we're broke, busted, and disgusted.

00:12:23.519 --> 00:12:25.508
We're never going to get anything.

00:12:25.508 --> 00:12:27.211
We're always going to be poor.

00:12:27.211 --> 00:12:33.599
Grandma was poor, we're poor, and my kids are going to be poor.

00:12:33.599 --> 00:12:35.554
" No, we are barrier breakers.

00:12:40.057 --> 00:12:41.550
Poverty stops with us.

00:12:41.550 --> 00:12:43.410
We're not having it ever again.

00:12:43.410 --> 00:12:44.880
We're not going to live in it.

00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:55.474
I am going to decree and declare that the blessing and the favor of God is on me, and that everything I put my hands to will prosper.

00:12:55.474 --> 00:13:02.240
Everything I do, Father, I'm anointed to do it, and you've appointed me for such a time as this.

00:13:05.946 --> 00:13:10.674
My angels are going out right now from the north, south, east, and west, and bringing my harvest in.

00:13:11.910 --> 00:13:16.320
I thank you, Holy Spirit, that you're bringing favor.

00:13:16.320 --> 00:13:18.457
Everywhere I go, I have favor.

00:13:18.457 --> 00:13:21.611
When I walk into a store, I have favor.

00:13:21.611 --> 00:13:32.200
Whenever I walk out of the store, I have favor because I'm blessed coming in, I'm blessed going out, I'm blessed in the city, and I'm blessed in the field.

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:50.089
You've got to believe it, but you've got to say it out of your mouth.

00:13:50.089 --> 00:13:51.339
Stop that milly-mouthed talking.

00:13:51.339 --> 00:13:57.824
Life and death is in the power of your tongue and you're eating the fruit of what you've been saying.

00:13:57.824 --> 00:13:59.947
Remember that, ladies and gentlemen.

00:13:59.947 --> 00:14:03.499
As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

00:14:13.964 --> 00:14:14.160
The Bible says as a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

00:14:14.160 --> 00:14:19.190
So don't take thoughts that contradict what you feel in your heart.

00:14:19.190 --> 00:14:22.509
Out of the abundance of the heart, the mouth speaks.

00:14:22.509 --> 00:14:26.840
The more you say it, the more you're going to reap it.

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:33.383
And you have more power over your seed than just the bad ground is what the Holy Spirit said to me.

00:14:43.199 --> 00:14:43.439
You need to know that.

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:48.649
He said, "Brenda, you can't just blame that on the preacher's ground.

00:14:48.649 --> 00:14:55.873
" He said, "There's a lot of them that are out there saying out of their mouth, 'Well, I never get a harvest.

00:14:55.873 --> 00:15:01.550
'" You need to learn, because I've learned to watch my words.

00:15:01.550 --> 00:15:10.364
I've never, since I've been raising my son in the last 16 years, said poverty out of my mouth.

00:15:10.862 --> 00:15:16.711
We refuse to live by the curse of the law.

00:15:19.555 --> 00:15:19.786
I'm blessed because Deuteronomy 28 says so.

00:15:21.897 --> 00:15:29.319
I believe that Isaac planted in famine and reaped a hundredfold that same year.

00:15:29.319 --> 00:15:36.935
I believe that God is no respecter of persons and that what he did for Isaac, he'll do for me.

00:15:46.880 --> 00:15:49.474
Isaac sowed in famine.

00:15:49.474 --> 00:15:52.880
Genesis 26, one of my favorite chapters.

00:15:52.880 --> 00:15:59.279
Isaac sowed in famine, and that same year he reaped a hundredfold.

00:15:59.279 --> 00:16:00.506
So he sowed in famine.

00:16:00.506 --> 00:16:03.600
There was no rain, but God still blessed it.

00:16:03.600 --> 00:16:10.280
It's not all just about the soil; it's what you believe and what you say out of your mouth.

00:16:10.280 --> 00:16:14.000
Life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:18.206
So you have to take authority over your words.

00:16:18.206 --> 00:16:28.423
You need to take communion and call crop failure over every bad word you've said, over every idle word of poverty, lack, and milly-mouthed talk like, "Oh, we're never going to get out of this house.

00:16:33.375 --> 00:16:38.590
" I always have the blessing on my life.

00:16:39.634 --> 00:16:40.011
Why?

00:16:40.011 --> 00:16:43.830
Because I believe in the covenant that God has given me.

00:16:44.160 --> 00:16:47.404
Greater is he that is in me than he that is in the world.

00:16:47.404 --> 00:16:51.725
And he's given me the ability and the power to get wealth with these hands.

00:16:51.725 --> 00:16:56.720
Show me, Holy Spirit, how to do it today.

00:16:56.720 --> 00:17:03.050
Give me wisdom on where I'm supposed to put my boat into motion.

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:06.149
Faith without works is dead.

00:17:06.149 --> 00:17:12.662
And if you're not doing something to bring it forth, your faith is not working.

00:17:12.662 --> 00:17:15.856
You are snared by the words of your mouth, too.

00:17:15.856 --> 00:17:22.680
So it all works like that big motor; it all ticks together.

00:17:22.680 --> 00:17:30.845
And if you're not walking in love and you're walking in strife and you're doing all the things, you're putting a dam on the blessing coming into your household.

00:17:30.845 --> 00:17:35.050
And I always come before covenant with this communion all the time.

00:17:35.050 --> 00:17:36.307
That's why we have it everywhere.

00:17:36.307 --> 00:17:41.939
I got sacks of them everywhere because I believe in the power of the blood of Jesus.

00:17:41.939 --> 00:17:45.929
I believe in the power of the communion and what he did for me.

00:17:46.533 --> 00:18:02.160
This is all about it right now, ladies and gentlemen: Palm Sunday going into the crucifixion of Good Friday and saying, "Jesus, thank you for what you did for me and you delivered me from Deuteronomy 28 according to your word.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:07.760
" He said in Galatians, "Christ has redeemed me from the curse of the law.

00:18:07.760 --> 00:18:13.560
" And this is what he'd redeemed me from: Deuteronomy 28 and all those curses down below it.

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:17.120
He redeemed me from every single one of those curses.

00:18:17.120 --> 00:18:24.754
Deuteronomy 28 says all those blessings will come upon those, and he redeemed me from every one of them.

00:18:24.754 --> 00:18:34.400
I'm not underneath the curse because Galatians says that Christ redeemed me from all the curses of Deuteronomy 28, ladies and gentlemen.

00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:36.400
And we don't have to walk in sickness.

00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:38.142
We don't have to walk in lack.

00:18:38.142 --> 00:18:39.462
We can walk in abundance.

00:18:39.462 --> 00:18:43.240
And that's why we have to speak and decree a thing out of our mouth.

00:18:43.240 --> 00:18:46.930
Say it because life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:18:46.930 --> 00:18:50.130
And faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:18:50.130 --> 00:18:52.276
And you have to speak it out your mouth.

00:18:52.276 --> 00:18:55.370
You have to say it out your mouth: "I believe.

00:18:55.370 --> 00:18:58.594
I receive a million-dollar check in the name of Jesus.

00:18:58.594 --> 00:19:02.194
" Stretch out there big—that's big to me.

00:19:02.194 --> 00:19:04.340
I'm believing for a $100,000 check.

00:19:04.340 --> 00:19:04.860
I believe.

00:19:04.860 --> 00:19:10.080
You say it out your mouth: "I believe for a $10,000 check.

00:19:10.080 --> 00:19:12.533
" You may just be at a $500 level.

00:19:12.533 --> 00:19:13.084
That's fine.

00:19:13.084 --> 00:19:14.050
Or a $100 level.

00:19:14.050 --> 00:19:15.560
I believe for a $100 check.

00:19:15.560 --> 00:19:17.360
Say it out your mouth.

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:21.828
And the more you say it, the more you believe it because your heart's going to start to change.

00:19:21.828 --> 00:19:23.679
You're going to start to change.

00:19:23.679 --> 00:19:30.992
It's like dumping in clean water: when you see the oil and the dirty water, you keep dumping in the clean, clean, clean, and eventually it keeps filtering.

00:19:30.992 --> 00:19:33.800
It'll filter all that mess out of you.

